title: For Sale:  Crusader gear Rear bag
postcontent: This is from crusader site! Long-range rifle shooters (and even short-range ones) know that consistency on target means taking yourself out of the stabilization equation and supporting that rifle with some sort of bipod, tripod, rest, or front & rear bags. We’ve long suffered with having to take multiple bags on trips to the range or into the field because you never know how much elevation you need your bags to provide. Crusader Gear has engineered a solution by making one bag that can be configured in a number of different ways in order to provide the maximum functionality. Use it flat when you just need a little, or fold it in half, use it like a mini A-frame, or stand it up on end when you need the most support under the buttstock or forend of your rifle. The one-inch webbing strap serves as a carry strap, a handle, or cinches the bag in half to help it maintain its position without slipping or flattening out. Crusader Gear’s Multi-Position Rifle Bag is constructed of 1000D Cordura nylon and filled with poly pellets that will not absorb moisture, so this bag will not get heavier in the rain or humid air. No more weighing down your rucksack, range bag or drag bag with multiple shooting bags. This one can do it all.
